  "mixStrategy": "This sleep-mode Classical arrangement is built around a gentle I\u2192IV\u2192V\u2192I then I\u2192vi\u2192IV\u2192V progression in C major, with each track occupying a distinct frequency band to create a warm, enveloping sonic blanket.\n\nFREQUENCY SEPARATION:\n- BASS (Cello, 20-300Hz, MIDI 36-48): Provides the harmonic foundation with sustained root notes and occasional 5ths. Very long notes (4-8s) anchoring each chord change. Sits in the sub-bass/bass region.\n- CHORDS (String Ensemble, 300Hz-2kHz, MIDI 48-67): Gentle sustained triads and 7th chords in close voicing. Provides the harmonic body with smooth voice leading \u2014 common tones are held across chord changes. Warm, pillowy pad.\n- MELODY (Acoustic Piano, 1-8kHz, MIDI 60-76): A lyrical, stepwise lullaby theme with long note values. Plays chord tones on strong beats, with gentle scalar passing tones. Very sparse \u2014 breathing space between phrases.\n- TEXTURE (Flute, 3kHz+, MIDI 72-84): Ethereal counter-melody fragments, extremely sparse. Provides shimmer and air. Responds to the piano melody in call-and-response fashion.\n\nENERGY ARC (6 segments of ~7.5s each):\n0-7.5s: 0.3 \u2014 Only bass and soft chords enter. Piano plays first note at end.\n7.5-15s: 0.4 \u2014 Piano melody enters gently, strings swell slightly.\n15-22.5s: 0.5 \u2014 Peak warmth. Flute enters. All four voices present.\n22.5-30s: 0.5 \u2014 Sustained fullness, second phrase of progression.\n30-37.5s: 0.4 \u2014 Gradual retreat. Flute thins out, velocities drop.\n37.5-45s: 0.3 \u2014 Final plagal/authentic cadence. Everything fades to near-silence.\n\nRHYTHMIC INTERLOCK: At 48 BPM, a quarter note = 1.25s. All tracks change chords together. The bass sustains through chord changes, the strings shift voicings smoothly, the piano places notes on beats 1 and 3, and the flute floats above with ornamental fragments offset from the piano. No drums \u2014 pure tonal warmth for sleep.\n\nCHORD TIMING (each chord ~5.625s = ~4.5 beats at 48BPM, 8 chords across 45s):\nC (0-5.6) \u2192 F (5.6-11.25) \u2192 G (11.25-16.9) \u2192 C (16.9-22.5) \u2192 C (22.5-28.1) \u2192 Am (28.1-33.75) \u2192 F (33.75-39.4) \u2192 G (39.4-45)",
